The paper focuses on developing a deep neural network architecture for recognizing state-action pairs from RGB-D data streams in robotic applications. This involves tasks such as trajectory recognition and learning from demonstration, which are central to the field of robotics (cs.RO). The use of RGB-D data streams also suggests a strong connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of deep neural networks, which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the evaluations include deployment on a physical robot, indicating a connection to systems and control (cs.SY).
